The paper deals with signal recovery from compressive measurements, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of group-sparsity as a signal model suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the analysis of random matrices, which is a common topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and statistics (cs.SI).
